Our company information security team (part of our legal department), is very supportive of our current Wiki initiative, and aware of the growing business interest in using the Wiki...in fact, their director has a seat on our Wiki Council (the decision-making body with responsibility to control/manage our Wiki).  They have come to us, and asked if there was an ability to do a query on "all" postings, comments, edits, attachments (hence, any wiki changes), for a given user.  This is, a use case, our legal department often finds itself engaged in.  That being, the "legal discovery on a given individual" use case.  They also have "legal discovery on a given set of keywords" use case, which the product already does, out-of-the-box, with its search capabilities.  So, the suggestion here, is that soon, with legal discovery issues being so active in corporate america, there will be demands on products like Confluence, to do this.  What do you think, is this a "hot" enhancement?

